\cf0 Thus, the agent has access to its own system information, its configuration, and each report it generates. \'a0The server has copies of all of this data, plus access to all of the Puppet modules, and any back-end databases and services that might be needed to compile the configuration.
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs30 Beyond the components that go into this workflow, which we\'92ll address next, there are many data types that Puppet uses for internal communication. These data types are critical, because they\'92re how all communication is done, and they\'92re public types and any other tools can consume or produce.
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs30 The most most important data types are:
